Sound Buddy — Licensing Overview
================================

Copyright (c) 2026 Patrick Robinson (on-par)

This repository is dual-licensed. Which license applies depends on which part
of the tree the code lives in:

1. Desktop application — proprietary (source-available)

   Everything under app/ — the Electron desktop app and the packaged
   application built from it — is licensed under the Sound Buddy Desktop
   Application License. See app/LICENSE. In short: the source may be read,
   but the application may only be used with a valid license key, and it may
   not be redistributed.

2. Everything else — MIT

   Everything in this repository outside app/ is licensed under the MIT
   License (reproduced below). That includes the packages under packages/ —
   each of which also carries its own copy of the MIT License —

     packages/shared            @sound-buddy/shared
     packages/scene-inspector   @sound-buddy/scene-inspector
     packages/audio-engine      @sound-buddy/audio-engine
     packages/ai-analyst        @sound-buddy/ai-analyst
     packages/cli               @sound-buddy/cli

   as well as the build and release scripts, CI configuration, shared
   TypeScript configuration, and documentation, so the MIT packages can be
   built and reused outside this repository.

Third-party software bundled with or used by Sound Buddy (including sox,
FFmpeg, the relocatable Python runtime, and Python libraries such as librosa,
numpy, and scipy) remains under its own respective licenses; nothing in this
repository's licenses alters them.

